org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers
Class LaTeXCompiler

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.jsbml.util.StringTools
      org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers.LaTeXCompiler
All Implemented Interfaces:
ASTNodeCompiler
public class LaTeXCompiler
extends StringTools
implements ASTNodeCompiler

Converts ASTNodeValue objects into a LaTeX String to be included into scientific writings or to be displayed in a GUI.

Since:
0.8
Version:
$Rev: 1250 $
Author:
Andreas Dräger

bottomrule

public static final String bottomrule
Requires LaTeX package booktabs. Produces a fancy line at the bottom of a table. This variable also includes the end{longtable} command and a new line.

eqBegin

public static final String eqBegin
Surrounded by new line symbols. Begin equation. This type of equation requires the LaTeX package breqn. It will produce equations with automatic line breaks (LaTeX will compute the optimal place for line breaks). Unfortunately, this does not work for very long denominators.

eqEnd

public static final String eqEnd
End equation; cf. eqBegin. Surrounded by new line symbols.

compile

public ASTNodeValue compile(String name)
Description copied from interface: ASTNodeCompiler
A compiler will also have to deal with a name. The meaning of this can be various. For instance, the name may refer to a Species in the system. In case of numerical computation, the ASTNodeCompiler must create an ASTNodeValue representing the current value of this Species.
